               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I met a person in Oxford-street, named Smith, with these things - he said he had tried to pawn them, but no person would take them in; he said he had had nothing to eat the whole morning; I gave him 6d., and went to offer them to pawn, and was detained; he lives at No. 110, Wardour-street - I have known him many years.</p>
